[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]A small immersion nudge — when the in-game day flips over, the keeper thinks about what day of the week it is and what's happening on it, so you don't walk right past merchant days or tavern nights.[/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][b]Daily thought[/b] — fires just after dawn, at the moment NPCs leave their houses to start their day. The thought shows the day name ("It's Monday...") and any known event on that day ("I could drop by the tavern").[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Event messages[/b] — include vendor visits, refugee deliveries, tavern nights, Gerry's runs, etc. Toggle them off if you prefer just the day name without the extra context.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Choose thought bubbles or floaty text[/b] — a speech-bubble style (like NPC interactions) or the usual XP-pop style above the keeper's head. Pick the one that fits your HUD preference.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Fully translated[/b] into ES, FR, IT, JA, KO, PL, PT-BR, RU, ZH-CN. For JA / KO / ZH-CN the game's floaty-text font doesn't include those glyphs, so those languages always use the speech-bubble path regardless of your setting.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/73]Bring Out Yer Dead[/url] — schedule the donkey's body deliveries for the time of day that suits you.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/53]Longer Days[/url] — stretch the day cycle so there's more time between daily-thought prompts.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/41]Save Now[/url] — includes "Save on New Day" so each daily thought coincides with a fresh save.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Languages[/b]

ES
FR
IT
JA**
KO**
PL
PT-BR
RU
ZH-CN**

**The game doesn't support the font for these languages for the standard floaty text, so users using these languages will get speech bubbles instead.[/size]
[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79][size=3]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack at Graveyard Keeper Nexus - Mods and community (nexusmods.com)[/size][/url]
[/list]
[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...&#92;steamapps&#92;common&#92;Graveyard Keeper&#92;BepInEx[/code][/size]

